subSubSection.paragraph:
SOLENOMERE (
slm
). Solenomore originating on apical side of telopodite, just after posttorsal narrowing, whiplike, taeniate, irregularly curving in specimens prepared for SEM, longitudinally fluted (sometimes indistinctly) and sometimes also with tiny retrorse spines in distal part. A slender proximal spine (
ps
) often originating from base of solenomere, sometimes accompanied by a small ± lamellar outgrowth and/or a second small spine.
